+# Exploration 002 Report - Recursive Closure And Spillover Audit
+
+## Goal
+
+Run the recursive exact closure audit on each canonical first-budget seed from
+Exploration 001 and determine, for each seed, the immediate mandatory
+conjugate-completion companions, the forced helical sign sectors and projected
+triad interactions that must be checked next, and whether the seed closes to a
+finite fixed point inside the current budget or spills beyond it.
+
+## Sources Used
+
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/GOAL.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/REASONING.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT-SUMMARY.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md`
+- `library/factual/navier-stokes/recursive-exact-closure-must-use-the-full-active-ledger-and-exact-projected-helical-coefficients.md`
+- `library/factual/navier-stokes/closure-forced-spectators-belong-on-the-exact-support-ledger-from-the-first-pass.md`
+- `library/factual/navier-stokes/exact-support-search-object-is-a-finite-canonical-helical-support-sheet-with-mandatory-conjugate-completion.md`
+- `library/factual/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/step-2-is-well-posed-once-the-phase-ledger-search-class-and-metric-sheet-are-frozen.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/code/closure_audit.py`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/code/output/closure_audit_summary.txt`
+
+## Operational Note
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Report skeleton created first and filled incrementally as the
+  audit proceeded.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exploration 001 now supplies the live first-budget catalog:
+  nondegenerate noncollinear one-triad helical seeds
+  `k = p + q`
+  in sign-sheet classes
+  `(+++)`,
+  `(++-)`,
+  `(+--)`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Repeated-wavevector and collinear configurations were already
+  excluded upstream. They are not live Step-2 seeds because the exact
+  projected interaction coefficient vanishes there.
+
+## Frozen Closure Rule Reused Here
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Step 1 froze the closure order:
+  1. add mandatory conjugates;
+  2. test every ordered pair on the full active ledger against exact projected
+     helical interactions;
+  3. add every nonzero forced target mode with its conjugate completion;
+  4. repeat until a fixed point or budget spill.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Closure-forced spectators belong on the support ledger from the
+  first pass. No visually tidy core may be kept by pruning those modes away.
+
+## Working Notes
+
+### Seed extraction
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` I imported the canonical seed catalog from Exploration 001
+  rather than inventing a new quotient rule in this report.
+- `[INFERRED]` The closure audit therefore has exactly three live seeds to
+  test, all on the same nondegenerate geometry class and distinguished only by
+  the canonical sign sheet.
+
+### Saved coefficient check
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` I saved
+  `code/closure_audit.py`
+  and ran it against two representative geometries:
+  one generic scalene triad and one equal-length noncollinear triad.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The output
+  `code/output/closure_audit_summary.txt`
+  shows nonzero exact projected coefficients for the original seed interaction
+  and for the first off-orbit targets generated by the mirror-complete ledger
+  in all three canonical sign-sheet classes.
+
+## Closure Audit
+
+### 1. Mandatory representation companions
+
+Take one live canonical seed
+
+```text
+tau_0 = ((k, sigma_k), (p, sigma_p), (q, sigma_q)),
+k = p + q,
+p != q,
+p not parallel to q.
+```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The raw seed first enlarges by mandatory conjugate completion to
+
+  ```text
+  S_0 = {
+    (k, sigma_k), (p, sigma_p), (q, sigma_q),
+    (-k, sigma_k), (-p, sigma_p), (-q, sigma_q)
+  }.
+  ```
+- `[INFERRED]` These mirror modes are mandatory representation companions, not
+  optional spectators.
+
+### 2. Ordered pairs that stay on the seed orbit
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The ordered pairs
+
+  ```text
+  (p, q) -> k,
+  (k, -p) -> q,
+  (k, -q) -> p
+  ```
+
+  and their mirrors reproduce the original triad orbit only.
+- `[INFERRED]` Self-pairs such as `(p, p)` do not rescue the budget:
+  the ambient exact interaction scalar
+
+  ```text
+  Gamma_{r,p,p}(u)
+    = -i overline{u^(r)} · [ (p · u^(p)) P_r u^(p) ]
+  ```
+
+  vanishes because divergence-free data satisfy
+  `p · u^(p) = 0`.
+
+### 3. First genuinely new off-orbit checks forced by the full ledger
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Once the ledger is mirror-complete, the first genuinely new
+  ordered-pair interactions that must be checked are:
+  1. `(p, -q)` and `(-p, q)`, targeting the orbit `±(p - q)`;
+  2. `(k, p)` and `(-k, -p)`, targeting the orbit `±(2p + q)`;
+  3. `(k, q)` and `(-k, -q)`, targeting the orbit `±(p + 2q)`.
+- `[INFERRED]` None of these wavevectors can lie back on the original orbit
+  `±p`,
+  `±q`,
+  `±k`
+  without forcing
+  `p = 0`,
+  `q = 0`,
+  `p = q`,
+  or collinearity, all excluded by the live seed catalog.
+
+### 4. What the saved exact coefficient checks establish
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The saved coefficient audit shows the following for both the
+  generic scalene and equal-length noncollinear representatives:
+  1. the seed interaction itself is nonzero in every canonical sign-sheet
+     class;
+  2. the new target orbit `±(p - q)` has nonzero projected coefficients in
+     both target helical sectors
+     `tau = +`
+     and
+     `tau = -`
+     for all three canonical sign-sheet classes;
+  3. the further targets
+     `±(2p + q)`
+     and
+     `±(p + 2q)`
+     also appear with nonzero projected coefficients in both target helical
+     sectors on those representative checks.
+- `[INFERRED]` Because the local record provides no exact pruning identity for
+  these target sectors, controller should treat both target signs on each new
+  wavevector orbit as live next checks.
+
+### 5. Immediate budget-spill mechanism
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The single off-orbit interaction `(p, -q) -> p - q` is already
+  enough to force spill beyond the first budget.
+- `[INFERRED]` Once `±(p - q)` and its live helical target sectors enter the
+  support ledger, the support is no longer one exact triad orbit inside the
+  frozen first budget.
+- `[INFERRED]` The additional targets
+  `2p + q`
+  and
+  `p + 2q`
+  strengthen the spill diagnosis, but they are not needed to decide the status.
+
+## Seed-By-Seed Status Table
+
+| Canonical seed | Mandatory companions | Next exact checks | Status | Decisive reason |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `(+++)` | `[VERIFIED]` add `(-k,+)`, `(-p,+)`, `(-q,+)` | `[VERIFIED]` check `±(p-q)`, `±(2p+q)`, `±(p+2q)` with both target signs | `budget spill` | `[INFERRED]` mirror-complete pair `(p,-q)` already forces the new orbit `±(p-q)` |
+| `(++-)` | `[VERIFIED]` add `(-k,+)`, `(-p,+)`, `(-q,-)` | `[VERIFIED]` check `±(p-q)`, `±(2p+q)`, `±(p+2q)` with both target signs | `budget spill` | `[INFERRED]` mirror-complete pair `(p,-q)` already forces the new orbit `±(p-q)` |
+| `(+--)` | `[VERIFIED]` add `(-k,+)`, `(-p,-)`, `(-q,-)` | `[VERIFIED]` check `±(p-q)`, `±(2p+q)`, `±(p+2q)` with both target signs | `budget spill` | `[INFERRED]` mirror-complete pair `(p,-q)` already forces the new orbit `±(p-q)` |
+
+## Dead Ends / Failed Attempts
+
+- `[INFERRED]` I initially treated equal-length noncollinear same-sign geometry
+  as a possible loophole where the first off-orbit coefficient might cancel.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The saved direct coefficient evaluation rejects that loophole:
+  the equal-length noncollinear representative still gives nonzero projected
+  coefficients for the original seed interaction and for the new target orbit
+  `p - q`
+  in all three canonical sign-sheet classes.
+
+## Final Findings
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Every live first-budget canonical seed has mandatory
+  conjugate-completion companions on the mirror triad orbit before closure can
+  begin.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The concrete next projected interactions forced by the full
+  active ledger are the off-orbit targets
+  `p - q`,
+  `2p + q`,
+  and
+  `p + 2q`,
+  together with their mirrors.
+- `[INFERRED]` The honest next sign-sector check on each of those new
+  wavevector orbits is two-sided:
+  both helical target sectors must stay on the ledger unless a later exact
+  identity kills one explicitly.
+- `[INFERRED]` No canonical live seed reaches a genuine finite fixed point
+  inside the current budget. All three end with the same sharp status:
+  `budget spill`.
+- `[INFERRED]` No live seed dies by representation dependence. Mirror choice
+  and `p <-> q` only relabel the same off-orbit wavevector classes.
+
+## Budget-Limited Verdict For Controller Review
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The first budget does not contain a genuinely closed one-triad
+  exact support ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` The sharpest earned current-budget negative is:
+  `recursive closure spills every live one-triad seed beyond the budget on the
+  first honest closure pass after conjugate completion`.
+- `[INFERRED]` There is no survivor here to hand to Chain Step 3. Any further
+  work should treat this as a budget-limited negative and decide explicitly
+  whether controller wants enlargement testing or escalation, rather than
+  silently promoting a cosmetically tidy one-triad picture.
